## Computer Use Configuration

This workflow includes steps that execute autonomously via the Computer Use Engine.

**Engine Initialization:** The engine detects the platform at runtime (WSL2, Linux, Windows, macOS) and loads the correct backend automatically.

**Available Methods:**
- `engine.screenshot()` -- capture full screen
- `engine.click(x, y)` / `engine.double_click(x, y)` / `engine.right_click(x, y)`
- `engine.type_text(text)` -- type a string
- `engine.key_press(*keys)` -- press key combination (e.g., "ctrl", "s")
- `engine.scroll(x, y, amount)` -- scroll at position
- `engine.drag(start_x, start_y, end_x, end_y)` -- drag
- `engine.find_element(description)` -- locate UI element by name
- `engine.get_screen_size()` -- get display dimensions

**Execution Commands:**
- `/execute-workflow` -- run this workflow via computer use
- `/pause-execution` -- pause mid-execution
- `/resume-execution` -- resume paused execution

**Config:** `computer_use/config.yaml` -- platform, provider, and action settings.

{{END_IF_COMPUTER_USE}}
